In the INTEREST OF: K.K.F., No. ED 106927 Missouri Court of Appeals, Eastern District, DIVISION ONE. FILED: July 30, 2019 FOR APPELLANT, Christopher M. Braeske, 8008 Carondelet Ave., Clayton, MO 63105. For Juvenile Officer, Respondent, Siobhan K. Akers, 105 South Central Ave., Clayton, MO 63105, Richard J. Childress, 111 North 7 th Street, Suite 329, St. Louis, MO 63101. Attorney for Natural Mother, Laura E. Sidel, 4542 West Pine Blvd, St. Louis, MO 63108. Before Roy L. Richter, P.J., Robert M. Clayton III, J., and Angela T. Quigless, J.

ORDER

PER CURIAM

F.J.F. ("Father") appeals from the judgment of the family court terminating his parental rights to his minor child, K.K.F. ("Child"), born in December of 2012. We have reviewed the briefs of the parties and the record on appeal and find no error of law. No jurisprudential purpose would be served by a written opinion. However, the parties have been furnished with a memorandum for their information only, setting forth the facts and reasons for this order.

The judgment is affirmed pursuant to Rule 84.16(b).
